@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@alex = course-alex-local-token
@riley = course-riley-local-token

### Start first: docker compose -f compose.qdrant.yml up -d
### Then run: ./mvnw spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=qdrant

### Seed source rows
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/seed

### Index the same application projection into Qdrant
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/index

### Inspect typed provider capabilities and vector counts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/readiness

### Prove Tenant Blue retrieval
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/quality/rag/golden
Authorization: Bearer {{alex}}

### Prove Tenant Red retrieval and exclusions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/quality/rag/golden
Authorization: Bearer {{riley}}

### Upsert through the existing trusted Data Sync boundary
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/articles
Authorization: Bearer {{alex}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "article-qdrant-sync",
  "title": "Register a hardware key",
  "body": "Register and verify the hardware key before revoking the previous method.",
  "category": "authentication"
}

### Delete source plus derived Qdrant evidence
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/knowledge/articles/article-qdrant-sync
Authorization: Bearer {{alex}}

### Inspect Qdrant directly; collection size must be 384
GET http://localhost:6333/collections/course_prod07__knowledge-article
